{"serial": "11054", "department_serial": 12, "code": "CL2046", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Buddhism and Chinese Literature", "ch": "佛教與中國文學"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["HSU, MING-CHIEN"], "ch": ["徐銘謙"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "A", "room": "103"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": true, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "中國文學系", "en": "Department of Chinese Literature"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 43, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "漢代以降，隨著佛教的潛移默化，佛學逐漸深入中國文化。在中印思想衝突與交融的過程中，各種佛教著述陸續產生，這些文本不但是佛教的、同時也是中國文學的載體。兩者關係因而愈加密切，無論是中國的詩歌、散文、小說、戲曲……等，都能在其中發現佛教的影響。本課程將帶領學生關注中國佛教文學的不同面向，精讀相關文獻，期許對佛教與中國文學的內涵有進一步的宏觀認識。", "en": "Since the Han Dynasty, Buddhism has become popular and influenced Chinese culture. In this process, various Buddhist writings were produced one after another. The connotations of those texts include Buddhism and Chinese literature, and their relevance is getting higher. Whether it is Chinese poetry, prose, novels, operas, etc., the influence of Buddhism can be found. This course will lead students to focus on different aspects of Chinese Buddhist literature, and read relevant articles. It is expected that students will have a further understanding of the connotation of Buddhism and Chinese literature."}, "outline": {"ch": "第01週：課程說明（含學期講義、參考書目、常用工具資料庫）\n第02週：佛教文學概說\n第03週：另一種佛典印象：《百喻經》與《賢愚經》\n第04週：佛典神通（一）：觀音與女性書寫\n第05週：佛典神通（二）：壺中人故事\n第06週：僧傳文學概述\n第07週：高僧散文（一）\n第08週：高僧散文（二）\n第09週：期中分組報告\n第10週：近體詩與佛教\n第11週：再論詩禪關係\n第12週：公案話頭中的禪文學\n第13週：文字禪概述\n第14週：佛教紀行文學（一）：《大唐西域記》選\n第15週：佛教紀行文學（二）：《洛陽伽藍記》選\n第16週：期末分組報告\n第17週：開國紀念日放假\n第18週：指定閱讀討論──《盧至長者因緣經》與明雜劇《一文錢》", "en": "Week 01: Course description (including semester handouts, bibliography, and common tools database)\nWeek 02: Overview of Buddhist literature\nWeek 03: Another impression of Sutra\nWeek 04: Psychic Power in Sutra (1): Avalokitesvara and female writing\nWeek 05: Psychic Power in Sutra (2): Stories of “Pot People“\nWeek 06: Overview of monk biography literature\nWeek 07: Essays by eminent monks (1)\nWeek 08: Essays by eminent monks (2)\nWeek 09: Midterm group report\nWeek 10: Regulated verse and Buddhism\nWeek 11: Rethinking the relationship between poetry and Chan\nWeek 12: Chan literature in Gong-an huatou\nWeek 13: Overview of Wen-tzu Chan\nWeek 14: Buddhist travelogues (1)\nWeek 15: Buddhist travelogues (2)\nWeek 16: Final report\nWeek 17: National Founding Day\nWeek 18: Assigned Reading"}, "textbook": {"ch": "教科書：自編講義\n參考書舉隅：\n蕭麗華、廖肇亨主編，《中國佛教文學史》上下冊（高雄：佛光文化，2023）。\n楊義，《中國敘事學》（北京：人民，2009）。\n孫昌武，《佛教與中國文學》（上海：上海人民，2007）。\n陳引馳，《佛教文學》（上海：上海人民美術，2003）。\n胡遂，《中國佛學與文學》（長沙：岳麓，1998）。", "en": "Textbook: Self-compiled handouts\nReference book: \nHsiao lihua and Liao chaoheng. History of Chinese Buddhist Literature. Kaohsiung: Fo Guang Press, 2023. \nYang yi. Chinese Narratology. Beijing: People‘s Press, 2009. \nSun changwu. Buddhism and Chinese Literature. Shanghai: Shanghai People‘s Press, 2007. \nChen yinchi. Buddhist literature. Shanghai: Shanghai People‘s Fine Arts Press, 2003. \nHu sui. Chinese Buddhism and Literature. Changsha: Yuelu Press, 1998."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "30", "en": "30"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "平時（含課堂討論與出席）40％；期中分組報告30％；期末分組報告30％。", "en": "Regular grades (including class discussions and attendance) - 40％; Mid-term group reports - 30％; Final group report - 30％."}, "officeHour": {"ch": "無", "en": "none"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "17+1", "en": "17+1"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "開學首週與修課學生商訂，另有指定閱讀佛典與相關明雜劇。", "en": "Discussions are held with students during the first week of school, and there are also assigned readings for Sutra and Ming zaju."}, "domain": {"ch": "古典文學\n\n\n、\n\n\n義理", "en": "古典文學\n\n\n、\n\n\n義理"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencie